label.value: Malignant Mixed Epithelial and Mesenchymal Neoplasm of the Cervix

value.value: A mixed epithelial and mesenchymal neoplasm that arises from the cervix. It is characterized by the presence of malignant mesenchymal elements and benign or malignant epithelial elements. This category includes adenosarcoma and carcinosarcoma.
A rare malignant mixed epithelial and mesenchymal neoplasm that arises from the cervix. It is characterized by the presence of malignant mesenchymal elements and benign epithelial elements.
An osteosarcoma usually arising from the metaphysis of long bones. It is characterized by the presence of small cells and osteoid production. The prognosis is usually unfavorable.
A rare, benign, polypoid neoplasm that arises from the cervix. It is characterized by the presence of epithelial and mesenchymal elements.

A rare, benign, usually polypoid neoplasm that arises from the cervix. It is characterized by the presence of a glandular component and a smooth muscle cell component. Variants include the endocervical-type, mesonephric-type, and atypical polypoid adenomyoma.

An adenomyoma that arises from the cervix and is characterized by the presence of endocervical mucinous glands and a smooth muscle cell component. There is no atypia or significant mitotic activity present.

An adenomyoma that arises from the cervix and is characterized by the presence of glands showing mesonephric differentiation and a smooth muscle cell component. There is no atypia or significant mitotic activity present.
An adenomyoma that arises from the cervix and is characterized by the presence of a glandular component exhibiting architectural complexity.
An adenomyoma that arises from the uterine corpus and is characterized by the presence of marked glandular architectural complexity. It may recur following excision.
An embryonal neoplasm arising from the cervix with morphologic features resembling Wilms tumor of the kidney.
An aggressive malignant tumor of melanocytic origin that arises from the cervix.

A squamous cell carcinoma arising from the esophagus.  It is associated with a long history of tobacco and alcohol abuse and is exceedingly rare before the age of 30.  The median age is around 65 in both males and females.  It is located mostly in the middle and lower third of the esophagus.  Grossly, polypoid, ulcerated, plaque-like and occult lesions have been described.  The microscopic features are the same as in other squamous cell carcinomas.  Any degree of differentiation may occur, and variation within a single tumor is common.  The prognosis is poor.
A nevus that arises from the cervix. It is characterized by the presence of benign, heavily pigmented dendritic melanocytes.
A non-neoplastic or neoplastic disorder that affects the cervix. Representative examples include cervicitis, endocervical polyp, and carcinoma.
A benign, precancerous, or malignant neoplasm that arises from the squamous epithelium of the vagina.
A squamous cell carcinoma that arises from the vagina and is characterized by the presence of keratin pearls. Intercellular bridges and cytoplasmic keratinization are usually present.

A squamous cell carcinoma that arises from the vagina and is characterized by the presence of polygonal squamous cells. Intercellular bridges and cytoplasmic keratinization may be present, but keratin pearls are absent.
A squamous cell carcinoma that arises from the vagina and is characterized by the presence of nests of malignant basaloid squamous cells with scant amounts of cytoplasm.
A chromosome band present on 1q
This gene plays a regulatory role in histone methyltransferase activity and transcription.
A squamous cell carcinoma that arises from the vagina and is characterized by a papillary growth pattern, hyperkeratosis, and koilocytosis.
SET and MYND domain-containing protein 3 (428 aa, ~49 kDa) is encoded by the human SMYD3 gene. This protein plays a role in both histone methylation and transcriptional regulation.

A malignant tumor with glandular differentiation arising predominantly from Barrett mucosa in the lower third of the esophagus.  Rare examples of esophageal adenocarcinoma deriving from ectopic gastric mucosa in the upper esophagus have also been reported.  Grossly, esophageal adenocarcinomas are similar to esophageal squamous cell carcinomas.  Microscopically, adenocarcinomas arising in the setting of Barrett esophagus are typically papillary and/or tubular.  The prognosis is poor.

A benign or malignant neoplasm that arises from the vagina and is characterized by the presence of neoplastic glandular epithelial cells.  Representative examples include adenoma, endometrioid adenocarcinoma, and clear cell adenocarcinoma.
A rare adenocarcinoma that arises from the vagina with histologic features resembling the endometrioid adenocarcinoma of the endometrium.
A rare adenocarcinoma that arises from the vagina with histologic features resembling cervical mucinous adenocarcinoma.
Vaginal adenocarcinoma that derives from Wolffian duct remnants and shows mesonephric differentiation.
Cervical adenocarcinoma that derives from Wolffian duct remnants and shows mesonephric differentiation. It is not associated with human papillomavirus infection.
A benign papilloma that arises from the vagina in infants and young women.
A glandular epithelial neoplasm that arises from the vagina and shows intestinal differentiation.
An adenoma that arises from the vagina and is characterized by a tubular architectural pattern.
An adenoma that arises from the vagina and is characterized by a tubulovillous architectural pattern.
An adenoma that arises from the vagina and is characterized by a villous architectural pattern.

An invasive cystic adenocarcinoma arising from the ovary.  It is characterized by the presence of malignant glandular epithelial cells which contain intracytoplasmic mucin.  The malignant cells invade the ovarian stroma and the cystic spaces contain mucoid material.  In a minority of cases both ovaries are involved by the tumor.  The prognosis for stage I tumors is excellent.  Patients with metastases usually have a poor prognosis.
A carcinoma that arises from the vagina and is characterized by the presence of malignant glandular and malignant squamous epithelial components.
An adenoid cystic carcinoma that arises from the vagina. Myoepithelial cells are usually not present.
A carcinoma that arises from the vagina and is characterized by the presence of nests of basaloid cells with focal glandular formations.
A rare small cell neuroendocrine carcinoma that arises from the vagina.
A carcinoma that arises from the vagina and is characterized by the lack of specific cellular differentiation.

A benign or malignant mesenchymal neoplasm that arises from the vagina.  Representative examples include leiomyoma, rhabdomyoma, leiomyosarcoma, endometrioid stromal sarcoma, and botryoid-type embryonal rhabdomyosarcoma.
A rare benign skeletal muscle neoplasm arising from the cervix. It is characterized by the presence of small nucleated rhabdomyoblasts within a fibrous and myxoid stroma.

A morphologic variant of embryonal rhabdomyosarcoma arising from the vagina.  It is characterized by the formation of a cambium layer in the affected tissue and polypoid nodules with an abundant myxoid stroma. It occurs in female adults.

A morphologic variant of embryonal rhabdomyosarcoma arising from the vagina.  It is characterized by the formation of a cambium layer in the affected tissue and polypoid nodules within an abundant myxoid stroma.

label.value: Vaginal Endometrioid Stromal and Related Neoplasms

value.value: A category of rare neoplasms that arise from the vagina. It includes low grade endometrioid stromal sarcoma and undifferentiated sarcoma.

An uncommon intraepithelial malignant neoplasm of eccrine or apocrine origin, arising from the vulva.  It usually affects post-menopausal women.  In approximately 10-20% of the cases there is an associated anorectal, or urothelial carcinoma or a skin appendage adenocarcinoma identified.  It presents as a red, eczematous lesion.  Microscopically, it is characterized by the presence of the typical Paget cells which are large, round cells with abundant cytoplasm and prominent nuclei.

label.value: Endometrioid Stromal Sarcoma of the Vagina

value.value: A rare sarcoma that arises from the vagina. This category includes low grade endometrioid stromal sarcoma and undifferentiated vaginal sarcoma.

label.value: Vaginal Low Grade Endometrioid Stromal Sarcoma

value.value: An infiltrating sarcoma that arises from the vagina.  It is characterized by the presence of cells that resemble endometrial stromal cells.
A high grade infiltrating sarcoma that arises from the vagina. It is characterized by the presence of malignant small spindle cells with scant cytoplasm.
A locally infiltrating, non-metastasizing vaginal angiomyxoma.  It may recur following resection.

label.value: Vaginal Mixed Epithelial and Mesenchymal Neoplasm

value.value: A benign or malignant neoplasm that arises from the vagina and is characterized by the presence of epithelial and mesenchymal elements.  This category includes benign mixed tumor, adenosarcoma, carcinosarcoma, and malignant mixed tumor resembling synovial sarcoma.
